This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama on June 8, 2011. The memorandum addresses the unexpected and urgent refugee and migration needs related to Libya and Côte d'Ivoire. President Obama determines that it is important to the national interest to provide assistance under the Migration and Refugee Assistance Act of 1962. The assistance, not exceeding $15 million, will be used to meet the urgent needs of refugees and migrants affected by the violence in Libya and Côte d'Ivoire. This includes contributions to international, governmental, and nongovernmental organizations, as well as payment of administrative expenses of the Bureau of Population, Refugees, and Migration of the Department of State. The memorandum concludes by authorizing and directing the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register.